{"title_page": "Luke Frost", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2018}}\n''' Luke Frost''' is an abstract painter living in [[Cornwall]], and is the son of the [[England|English]] painter [[Anthony Frost]] and the grandson of [[Sir Terry Frost]].\n\nHis work featured in the \"Art Now Cornwall\" exhibition, at [[Tate St Ives]], 2007, and he was Artist in Residence at Tate St Ives in 2008 following with a solo show from 24 January to 4 May 2009 .\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Cornwall}}\n* [[List of St. Ives artists]]\n* [[Anthony Frost]]\n* [[Terry Frost]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.lukefroststudio.com Artists website]\n*[https://www.theguardian.com/arts/cornwallartistofthemonth/gallery/0,14609,1244739,00.html Guardian/Seen Cornwall feature]\n*[http://www.lukefroststudio.com/essays.htm Essays on Luke Frost by Matthew Collings, Tony Godfrey, Susan Daniel-McElroy, Michael Klein and others]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Frost, Luke}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Cornish people]]\n[[Category:20th-century English painters]]\n[[Category:English male painters]]\n[[Category:21st-century English painters]]\n[[Category:Abstract expressionist artists]]\n[[Category:St Ives artists]]\n\n\n{{UK-artist-stub}}\n{{England-painter-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2018}}\n''' Luke Frost''' is an abstract painter living in [[Cornwall]], and is the son of the [[England|English]] painter [[Anthony Frost]] and the grandson of [[Sir Terry Frost]].\n\nHis work featured in the \"Art Now Cornwall\" exhibition, at [[Tate St Ives]], 2007, and he was Artist in Residence at Tate St Ives in 2008 following with a solo show from 24 January to 4 May 2009 .\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of St. Ives artists]]\n* [[Anthony Frost]]\n* [[Terry Frost]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.lukefroststudio.com Artists website]\n*[https://www.theguardian.com/arts/cornwallartistofthemonth/gallery/0,14609,1244739,00.html Guardian/Seen Cornwall feature]\n*[http://www.lukefroststudio.com/essays.htm Essays on Luke Frost by Matthew Collings, Tony Godfrey, Susan Daniel-McElroy, Michael Klein and others]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Frost, Luke}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Cornish people]]\n[[Category:20th-century English painters]]\n[[Category:English male painters]]\n[[Category:21st-century English painters]]\n[[Category:Abstract expressionist artists]]\n[[Category:St Ives artists]]\n\n\n{{UK-artist-stub}}\n{{England-painter-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Gazamp", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSee also:AddedPortal:Cornwall", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luke_Frost"}
{"title_page": "Sam Smith discography", "text_new": "{{Use British English|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}}\n{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist         = [[Sam Smith]]\n| Image          = Sam Smith Lollapalooza 2015-7 (cropped 2).jpg\n| Caption        = Smith performing in [[Berlin]], Germany at [[Lollapalooza]] in 2015\n| Studio         = 2\n| EP             = 1\n| Singles        = 29\n| Option         = 1\n| Option name    = Remix albums\n| 1Option        = 2\n| 1Option name   = Promotional singles\n}}\n\nEnglish singer [[Sam Smith]] has released two [[studio album]]s, one [[remix album]], one [[extended play]], twenty-nine [[single (music)|single]]s (featuring on eight singles), and two [[promotional single]]s.\n\n''[[In the Lonely Hour]]'', Smith's debut album, was released in May 2014. They debuted in October 2012 featuring on English electronic duo [[Disclosure (band)|Disclosure]]'s single \"[[Latch (song)|Latch]]\", which peaked at number 11 on the [[UK Singles Chart]]. In February 2013 \"[[Lay Me Down (Sam Smith song)|Lay Me Down]]\" as the lead single from the album. In May 2013 they featured on [[Naughty Boy]]'s single \"[[La La La (Naughty Boy song)|La La La]]\". The single was released on 19 May 2013 and peaked to number one in the UK. In October 2013 they released their first EP ''[[Nirvana (EP)|Nirvana]]''. \"[[Money on My Mind]]\" was released as the second single from the album on 16 February 2014, the song peaked to number one on the UK Singles Chart. \"[[Stay with Me (Sam Smith song)|Stay with Me]]\" was released as the third single from the album on 14 April 2014, the song peaked to number one on the UK Singles Chart. \"[[I'm Not the Only One]]\" was the album's fourth single it was released on 31 August 2014, peaking to number 3 on the [[UK Singles Chart]]. \"[[Like I Can]]\" was released as the album's fifth single on 5 December 2014, peaking at number 9 on the [[UK Singles Chart]], becoming Smith's fourth consecutive top-ten hit as a lead artist in the UK.\n\nA re-release of \"Lay Me Down\" was released as the sixth single from the album on 22 February 2015, peaking at number 15 on the UK Singles Chart. In the same month Smith recorded another version of the song, featuring [[John Legend]], for the British charity television [[Comic Relief]], the song reached number one in the UK. In July 2015 they featured on [[Disclosure (band)|Disclosure]]'s single \"[[Omen (Disclosure song)|Omen]]\", peaking to number 13 in the UK. On 8 September 2015, Smith confirmed that their new song \"[[Writing's on the Wall (Sam Smith song)|Writing's on the Wall]]\" would be the theme song to the 24th [[James Bond in film|James Bond]] film ''[[Spectre (2015 film)|Spectre]]''. The song was released on 25 September 2015 and became the first Bond theme ever to go to number one in the UK. Their second album, ''[[The Thrill of It All (Sam Smith album)|The Thrill of It All]]'', followed in 2017 and topped the charts in the United Kingdom, Canada, Ireland, the Netherlands, New Zealand, Sweden, and the United States. Its lead single \"[[Too Good at Goodbyes]]\" reached number one in the United Kingdom, Australia, and New Zealand and also reached the top 5 in Canada, Denmark, the Netherlands, and the United States.\n\n==Albums==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"10\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\"| Sales\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:14em;\"| [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:85%;\"| [[UK Albums Chart|UK]]<br/><ref name=\"UK\">Peak positions in the United Kingdom: \n* For all except noted: {{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/21501/sam-smith/|title=Sam Smith full Official Chart History|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=5 October 2017}}\n* \"God Only Knows\": {{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/45404/brian-wilson-and-various-artists/|title=Brian Wilson & Various Artists full Official Chart History|publisher=Official Charts Company|accessdate=5 October 2017}}\n* \"Do They Know It's Christmas?\": {{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/45551/band-aid-30/|title=Band Aid 30 full Official Chart History|publisher=Official Charts Company|accessdate=5 October 2017}}\n* \"Latch (Acoustic)\": {{cite web|url=http://zobbel.de/cluk/140906cluk.txt|title=Chart: CLUK Update 6.09.2014 (wk35)|publisher=Zobbel.de|author=Tobias Zywietz|accessdate=5 October 2017}}\n* \"Together\": {{cite web|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/131207cluk.txt|title=Chart: CLUK Update 7.12.2013 (wk48)|publisher=Zobbel.de|author=Tobias Zywietz|accessdate=5 October 2017}}\n* \"Leave Your Lover\" and \"Make It to Me\": {{cite web|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/140607cluk.txt |title=Chart: CLUK Update 7.06.2014 (wk22)|publisher=Zobbel.de|author=Tobias Zywietz|accessdate=5 October 2017}}\n* \"Drowning Shadows\": {{cite web|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/151114cluk.txt |title=Chart: CLUK Update 14.11.2015 (wk46)|publisher=Zobbel.de|author=Tobias Zywietz|accessdate=5 October 2017}}\n* \"How Will I Know\": {{cite web|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/160716cluk.txt |title=CHART: CLUK Update 16.07.2016 (wk28)|publisher=Zobbel.de|author=Tobias Zywietz|accessdate=5 October 2017}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:85%;\"| [[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br/><ref name=\"AUS\">Peak positions for Australia:\n* For all except noted: {{cite web|url=http://www.australian-charts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Sam+Smith|title=Discography Sam Smith|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=5 October 2017}}\n* \"Money on My Mind\": {{cite web|url=http://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/23790/20140517-0000/Issue1262.pdf|title=ARIA Report: Issue 1262 (Week Commencing