's Alright]]\"\n| 2009\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Lay Me Down (Sam Smith song)|Lay Me Down]]\"\n<!--STOP!: You cannot justify merging the best bits of 3 different release into one single! All 3 releases charted differently in different territories and have different certifications! Almost every territory classes all 3 versions as different releases into the discography of Sam Smith including Sam Smith himself, that is why he (or his production team) titled the re-releases \"re-releases\"!-->\n| 2013\n| 46 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014{{efn|group=upper-alpha|\"Lay Me Down\" originally did not enter the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 on its first release, but peaked at number 25 on the Bubbling Under Hot 100 Singles chart.<ref name=\"US-Bubbling-singles\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/sam-smith/chart-history/bubbling-under-hot-100 |title=Sam Smith \u2013 Chart Results: Bubbling Under Hot 100 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=19 December 2017}}</ref>}}\n|\n| ''Nirvana''\n<!--STOP!: Do not revert the album of this song to \"In the Lonely Hour\" as at the original release of \"Lay Me Down\", \"In the Lonely Hour\" did not exist! This is why \"Lay Me Down\" was released from the EP \"Nirvana\" as this was the album that Sam Smith was working on at the time!-->\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Money on My Mind]]\"\n| rowspan=\"5\"| 2014\n| 1 || 51 || \u2014 || 18 || 11 || 4 || 32 || 12 || 18 || \u2014{{efn|group=upper-alpha|\"Money on My Mind\" did not enter the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, but peaked at number 7 on the Bubbling Under Hot 100 Singles chart.<ref name=\"US-Bubbling-singles\"/>}}\n|\n* BPI: Platinum<ref name=\"BPI\"/>\n* BVMI: Gold<ref name=\"BVMI\"/>\n* GLF: 2\u00d7 Platinum<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sverigetopplistan.se/netdata/ghl002.mbr/artdata?dfom=20140101&sart=3881498|title=Sa